cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.GR, cs.HC, cs.IR 

This paper deals with computer vision techniques such as object recognition and semantic segmentation to create cinemagraphs. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions collaborative learning and human preferences, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The use of optimization methods and evaluation of multiple candidates could also be relevant to cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
